{
  "stem": "24137.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I remember dying people, dying all at the time, not just from getting killed, but from dying from, from sickness, from starvation.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Because after a while, we couldn't make it to the bathrooms anymore.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So we just had to go outside.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And to get out of our barrack, to go to find a empty space, we had to go over these dead bodies.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And there were so many just bodies and bodies and bodies, dead.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And I also remember that in the morning, every day, they would have us go through lines.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And at the head of the line-- there were two lines-- at the head of the line were two Nazis or Gestapos or whatever you call them.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And they would say to the right, to the left, to the right, to the left.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I don't remember what was to the-- to life and what was to death.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But one of the lines, we never saw these people again.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And one of the other lines, you again got the chance tomorrow to go again through the same thing.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And I remember that I got a ear infection, terrible ear aches, terrible, terrible, terrible-- and pus just running down my, my head.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And we were sleeping on some kind of a mattresses that were filled with hay and my aunt taking the hay, and crushing it up, and sticking it in my ear, and saying you must not let that pus run down your ear.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Because if you do, you're going to go on the line that's for death.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And don't cry about it that it hurts you.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And if they ask you anything, don't say.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I remember we were going through these lines.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
